<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="383" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                                </head>
                                <p>This meeting is recorded in the Log, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>,
                                        <ref target="#pg_840">p. 840</ref>. While no record of the
                                    discussion has been found, the principal subject was presumably
                                    the attack led by Gibson which had destroyed the Möhne and Eder
                                    Dams. See Churchill, <hi rend="italic">Closing the Ring</hi>, p.
                                    68.</p>
                            </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>